Halt to DPRK-Targeted U.S. War Exercises Demanded Worldwide 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Reckless nuclear war exercises being staged by the U.S. and warmongers of south Korea against the DPRK are now under fire by broad public circles of the world.
 The Vanguard Party of Indonesia said in a statement released on Mar. 28 that the war maneuvers provocative and aggressive in their nature and scale go to prove that the U.S. remains unchanged in its wild ambition to isolate and stifle the DPRK and the U.S. is chiefly to blame for blocking the reconciliation, cooperation and peaceful reunification between the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. is truly interested in the peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula and in the solution to the nuclear issue, it should stop its reckless exercises for a war of aggression at once and withdraw its aggressor forces from south Korea, the statement urged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Sukarno Educational Foundation of Indonesia in a statement issued on the same day noted that the exercises for a war of aggression now under way across south Korea are increasing the danger of a nuclear war on the Korean Peninsula, demanding the U.S. and the south Korean authorities stop the reckless war moves at once.
 The Sri Lanka-People's Korea Friendship Association and the Sri Lanka Committee for the Reunification of Korea noted in a joint statement issued on Mar. 27 branded the military threat to the DPRK, a sovereign state, as a dangerous act of violating international law and the exercises being staged by the south Korean authorities against their compatriots in collusion with the U.S. as a crude breach of the spirit of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.

8th Kimilsungia Festival to Be Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The 8th Kimilsungia Festival will be held in Pyongyang on the occasion of the Day of the Sun (April 15), the birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung.
 It will prove to be a flower festival for praising the great man, a great political festival of loyalists as it will demonstrate internally and externally the firm faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to eternally hold Kim Il Sung in high esteem and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche that started in Mt. Paektu under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will be held at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition from April 13 to 20, Juche 95 (2006). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will bring together many organizations including military organs, ministries and national institutions, individual working people, youth and students, overseas Koreans and foreigners.

North Side's Committee for Implementation of June 15 Joint Declaration Meets 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- A general meeting of the north side's committee for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration took place in Pyongyang on Mar. 30.
 Present there were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly who is also honorary co-chairman of the north side's committee, Kim Ki Nam, vice-chairman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland who is secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Ro Tu Chol and Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, and Ryu Mi Yong, chairperson of the Central Committee of the Korean Chondoist Chongu Party, who are honorary co-chairpersons of the north side's committee and An Kyong Ho, chairman of the north side's committee, vice-chairmen and members of the committee, members of the sub-committees, members of the North Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting discussed its agenda item "On the orientation of activities of the north side's committee to energetically conduct the three-point patriotic movements under the banner of 'By our nation itself'". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An Kyong Ho made a report which was followed by speeches.
 The reporter and speakers said that in the last one year the "June 15 joint national committee" has played an important role in conducting the movement for national reunification as required by its mission and duty as a nationwide organization for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon those who love the country and the nation to keep pace and cooperate with one another to widen the scope of solidarity activities on the principle of subordinating everything to the efforts to accomplish the cause of national reunification, irrespective of ideology, system and party affiliation, political view and religious belief.
 To this end it is necessary for the committee to intensify the movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity and thoroughly implement the June 15 joint declaration true to the idea of "By our nation itself", they noted.
 A resolution was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed the discussion of an organizational matter.
 The meeting held a by-election of honorary co-chairpersons, vice-chairpersons and members of the north side's committee.

Rodong Sinmun on Socialism Based on Collectivism 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Socialism is the most advantageous society for the people among those of different types established in human history and the essential advantage of socialist society rests on collectivism.
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Genuine democracy is only socialist democracy based on collectivism, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialist democracy puts forward the popular masses as the master of state and society and helps them enjoy their freedom and rights as the master of all fields of social life to their heart's content. Under socialist society the popular masses lead a worthwhile life as the proud master of the state sovereignty and means of production, creating and enjoying material wealth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People demand that they glorify their social and political life and live amid the love and trust of social collectives. It is possible only under the socialist society in which the popular masses take the position of master. It is because socialism embodies the relations of comradely unity and cooperation, love and trust in all fields of social life.
 Only socialist society makes it possible to strengthen the unity and cooperation of the collectives, enhance the creative enthusiasm of all members of the collectives and sufficiently meet the independent demands of the collectives and individuals altogether.
 The advantages of socialist society can be seen in the reality of the DPRK. The advantages of Korean-style socialism centering on the popular masses have their essential source in the might of the single-minded unity of the leader, the Party and the masses. The Korean army and people, single-heartedly united around the headquarters of the revolution, have devoted their all to the prosperity and rosy future of the country. It is the features of Korean society that all the people form a big harmonious family to help and lead forward each other and devote themselves to society and the collectives. Korean-style socialism is the advantageous socialism in which all the people become the master of everything, everything serves them and their independent and creative life is kept in full bloom.

Rodong Sinmun on Source of Invincibility of Korean-Style Socialism 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates a signed article to the 24th anniversary of the publication of leader Kim Jong Il's famous work "On the Juche Idea."
 In the past 24 years the validity, truth and vitality of the Juche idea have been clearly proved, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea is the lifeline and the source of the invincible might of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It serves as an undying banner which made Korean-style socialism the most advantageous one centered on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the whole course of socialist construction the Workers' Party of Korea has held fast to the principle of making everything serve the popular masses, proceeding from the requirements of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are now dynamically stepping up the general march for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with love for their socialist system which ensures them human dignity and rights, worthwhile life and happiness. They will never barter Korean-style socialism, their life and soul, for anything else.
 The Juche idea is a militant banner that helped Korean-style socialism shine as the socialism of national independence firmly guaranteeing independence of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our Party and people have built socialism our own way according to our independent viewpoint and faith under the banner of Juche, not relying on any existing theories or others' experience. Thus they could successfully build in this land a powerful socialist state, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, which defends independence of the country and the nation.
 The Juche idea is a powerful ideological weapon which provided the firm revolutionary forces enough to defend and accomplish the cause of socialism to the end.
 The Songun idea of the Party with its root on the Juche idea serves as a militant banner which made Korean-style socialism shine as an invincible socialism with everlasting viability. As the Songun idea illuminates the road ahead, in our country the unity of the army and people based on the revolutionary soldier spirit has been firmly materialized, the single-minded unity of the Party and the revolutionary ranks strengthened on a high level and powerful military capacity provided to firmly defend the gains of socialism achieved with blood.

DPRK's Just Measure for Self-Defence Hailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Ministry of People's Security issued warrants of arrest for Fumiaki Yamata, Hiroshi Kato, Takayuki Noguchi and Ri Yong Hwa who were directly involved in the abduction of DPRK citizens in broad daylight in the guise of members of a "non-governmental organization."
 Minju Joson Friday in a signed commentary says that it is a very justifiable measure to defend the sovereignty of the DPRK and the interests of its citizens from the Japanese reactionaries' escalated hostile moves against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Terming the above-said persons the criminals who were directly involved in abducting DPRK citizens including returnees to their homeland from Japan and their children and Japanese women in the DPRK, the commentary goes on:
 What matters is that the abduction of DPRK citizens was by no means an accidental crime perpetrated by individual figures or organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This was obviously a product of the deliberate, premeditated and organized crime perpetrated at the instigation of the Japanese government and under its backing and patronage, pursuant to its hostile policy towards the DPRK.
 The Korean people are becoming increasingly assertive that the DPRK should take a strong countermeasure including a physical retaliation against the Japanese reactionaries' hostile policy towards it and their plots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accordingly, the DPRK Ministry of People's Security issued warrants for the arrest of the persons concerned as the first step according to the relevant articles of the DPRK criminal law and the criminal procedure law and demanded the Japanese government extradite the criminals to the DPRK through a relevant channel.
 There is no reason for Japan that claims to be a "law-abiding state" to turn down the just demand of the DPRK.

Angling Encouraged in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Angling becomes brisk in the large and small rivers, lakes and reservoirs in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea with the beginning of spring.
 Angling has a long history in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, along with agriculture, collection of edible plants and hunting, was a mainstay for the Korean people from the Neolithic era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People in the era used a fishing hook similar to the present one.
 The hook had an eye to tie up line and the point with a barb was sharpened.
 There was anchor-shaped fishing hook, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The materials of hooks were animal bones or teeth. The sizes of hooks were 3 centimeters or 5-8 centimeters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are big and small fishing hooks and fish bones of Myongthae (pollack), codfish, herring, gray mullet and mackerel among the remains of the Neolithic era. They show that the then people angled for various kinds of fishes, big and small, in rivers and seas.
 Many angling places have come into being in different parts of the country and rivers and reservoirs are teeming with fishes. Angling fans are growing in number day by day and national angling contests are organized every year. All this is ascribable to the government's policy of encouraging the angling custom with a long history.

General Meeting of C.C., North Headquarters of Pomminryon Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- A general meeting of the Central Committee of the North Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminryon) took place here on Friday.
 Present there were presidium members  of the North Headquarters of Pomminryon and members of the central committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general meeting informed its participants of an extraordinary meeting of co-chairmen of Pomminryon held recently and discussed measures for implementing decisions of the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general meeting underlined the need for the North Headquarters of Pomminryon to conduct a more dynamic movement for national reunification this year, holding high the slogan "Let us vigorously forward the patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity under the banner of 'By our nation itself'!" so as to discharge the mission and duty of Pomminryon for the times and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general meeting held a by-election of some presidium members of the North Headquarters of Pomminryon and central committee members.
